 "title": "Hiberno",
 "transtitle": "Hibernating",
 "author": "Elvira Sastre",
 "translator": "Mira Revesz",
 "poem": "Siempre que dormíamos era invierno, y en el frío me enseñabas a volar y yo te echaba de menos. Entonces despertaba. Y te echaba de menos. La primavera no quiere que los amores de invierno terminen, pero el verano ha llegado y ha arrasado con todo. Ahora tú solo sabes hablar del sol, te haces un moño despeinado mientras bostezas, te pintas las uñas de los pies, te ríes mucho más que antes, y, mientras, me dejas de querer. Ahora yo me vuelvo a refugiar en los poemas y escribo sobre febrero, echo de menos la lluvia y el sabor de tu jersey, y, mientras, te quiero más que ayer.",
 "transpoem": "Each time that we were sleeping it was winter, and in the cold you would teach me how to fly and I would miss you. Then I’d wake up. and keep missing you. Spring doesn’t want wintertime loving to end but summer has arrived and it’s swept everything away. Now you only know how to talk about the sun, you make a messy bun while you yawn, you paint your toes, you laugh much more than before, and, meanwhile, you stop loving me. Now I return to the refuge of poems. I seek their shelter and write about February, I miss the rain and the taste of your sweatshirt, and, meanwhile, I love you more than yesterday.",
