 "transpoem": "When I go I’d like to have had my turn at my life Loved to have loved freely passionately and not at all to have loved endlessly to the end And still holding forever Since when I leave to go to bed as I should I dream all the dreams I picture all the faces they’re laughing round square or raining ~ I fight back because I am not tough I fight back for you me us you they Everything that pushes pulls on my heartstrings to undo me I’ve made a list of things to forget we’ll want for nothing The bells can ring on this dog’s life we’ll have our fool’s wine we’ll have a good time",
